title: St Thomas-a-Watering
description: Mentioned by Chaucer in The Canterbury Tales (1386). It was here that the pilgrims crossed a stream which ran approximately along Albany Road. The adjacent building (322 Old Kent Road) was until recently the "Thomas a Beckett" pub, named after the 12th Century Archbishop of Canterbury whose murder led to the establishment of the pilgrimage shrine.

title: 187 Camberwell Grove
description: 187 Camberwell Grove. This semi-detached house was used in the UK TV hit series "Dempsey and Makepeace" (1984-1986) as the residence of Sgt. Harriet Makepeace (character played by Glynis Barber). The character of her counterpart, Lt. James Dempsey (former NYPD), was played by Michael Brandon. Glynis and Michael are a married couple since 1989.
